cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel variational model based on graph convolutional autoencoders for street-level air quality inference using data collected by mobile stations. This involves matrix completion and spatio-temporal correlation of the measurements. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these sub-categories deal with machine learning models and algorithms. The paper also involves graph-based methods, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of autoencoders and neural networks makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
